packagedElement.name: Store previous serial number and windspeeds together in container datatype

properties.documentation: output to file or plot a graph
RIght, here goes, should be straightforward enough...
oh crumbs, now I've got some slightly different data which needs a tweak here and there...

Example input:
5 3 2 1
first loop through swap first pair 3 5 2 1 swap second pair 3 2 5 1 swap third pair 3 2 1 5
second loop through swap first pair 2 3 1 5 swap second pair 2 1 3 5 third pair OK
third loop through swap first pair 1 2 3 5 second pair OK third pair OK
This is a bubble sort: it is very inefficient for large amounts of data.

<sub>put message on user interface with instructions</sub> <sub>start a loop e.g. while (flag==true)</sub> <sub> ask user to enter a number or 'x', and then press 'return'</sub> <sub> if (isValid(input)) //ie it's a number or an 'x'</sub> <sub> if (input != 'x')</sub> <sub> store the number</sub> <sub> else //it's an 'x'</sub> <sub> get out of the loop e.g. set flag=false</sub> <sub> else //it wasn't valid</sub> <sub> tell the user</sub> <sub> </sub><sub>if (numbers > 1) // this is a little addition to the design to handle a possible boundary case</sub> <sub> sort the numbers</sub> <sub> print to screen</sub> <sub>else</sub> <sub> tell the user they didn't put in enough numbers to sort</sub>
